MBOMBELA- A 40-year-old teacher from a school in Bushbuckridge in Mpumalanga, has been suspended for allegedly having a sexual relationship with a 15-year-old girl who is a pupil at the same school, the provincial Basic Education department said on Wednesday. He has been suspended today with immediate effect on full pay, said spokesman for the department, Jasper Zwane. It is alleged that the teacher has a sexual relationship with the pupil. The pupil is still attending the same school. We don t have more details on this matter as we are still investigating it. READ: KZN teacher suspended for allegedly having sex with pupilsZwane told the African News Agency (ANA) that the teacher would be subjected to an internal disciplinary hearing, after which the department would formulate the charges against him. He said the department had sent psychologists to the school to assess the state of the pupil and to draft a report.The suspension of the teacher comes at a time when the department is set to release a final report of an investigation into an incident that happened at a school in Mhluzi township in Middelburg late last year which left a 14-year-old pupil paralysed.She was allegedly assaulted by a teacher after he accused her of stealing R150. The teacher was suspended in January and the department started an investigation into the matter.Zwane told ANA that a preliminary report into an investigation had revealed that the child may have been assaulted. He said the department would release the final report later this week.African News Agency